  <title>get_abs_allocation_vertices</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts([Clutter.Vertex])
@returns(none)
def get_abs_allocation_vertices(verts)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Calculates the transformed screen coordinates of the four corners of
the actor; the returned vertices relate to the <link xref="Clutter.ActorBox">Clutter.ActorBox</link>
coordinates  as follows:
&lt;itemizedlist&gt;
&lt;listitem&gt;&lt;para&gt;v[0] contains (x1, y1)&lt;/para&gt;&lt;/listitem&gt;
&lt;listitem&gt;&lt;para&gt;v[1] contains (x2, y1)&lt;/para&gt;&lt;/listitem&gt;
&lt;listitem&gt;&lt;para&gt;v[2] contains (x1, y2)&lt;/para&gt;&lt;/listitem&gt;
&lt;listitem&gt;&lt;para&gt;v[3] contains (x2, y2)&lt;/para&gt;&lt;/listitem&gt;
&lt;/itemizedlist&gt;</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>verts :</p></td>
<td><p>Pointer to a location of an array of 4 <link xref="Clutter.Vertex">Clutter.Vertex</link> where to store the result.</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 0.4</p>
